---
title: Asparagus and Prosciutto Tartines with Lemon Pepper Ricotta and a Potato Hash
description: Yes, tartine is just another word for an open-faced sandwich. But for some reason, when you say it, that mishmash of ingredients on a piece of bread suddenly seems all the more special. And this morning-friendly tartine is very special, thanks to pieces of salty prosciutto, a lemony ricotta spread, and a hearty asparagus potato hash.
